oc:kn_1bd84348 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When authoring skill directives that agents must follow without exception" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use absolute language ('ALWAYS'/'NEVER') rather than soft language ('should'/'try to') when writing rules that must resist rationalization under pressure." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Absolute language creates clear boundaries that resist the agent's tendency to rationalize shortcuts under user pressure" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_39d1a0bb a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When bulletproofing critical skills where failure has high cost" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Redundancy is a feature, not a bug. Repeat critical mandates in overview, when_to_use, individual phases, and implementation rules — each context catches a different moment of temptation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A rule seen once is easily rationalized away; the same rule encountered at the moment of temptation is far harder to ignore" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_73bc1dc4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing skill rules for any process where users may apply time pressure" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Include pressure-resistant language in skill rules: 'even if faster', 'even if I seem in a hurry', 'STOP and re-analyze'. Design for the worst-case scenario, not the calm one." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Users under pressure will explicitly ask agents to skip steps; rules must explicitly address this scenario" .

oc:kn_74f57a66 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing skills with known failure modes or common shortcuts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Include explicit anti-patterns showing exactly what shortcuts look like, so agents experience cognitive friction when tempted to take them." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Listing anti-patterns creates a pattern-matching defense — the agent recognizes its own rationalization as a known bad pattern" .

oc:kn_db493c60 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing multi-phase processes where phase-skipping is a known failure mode" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Structural defenses are stronger than textual ones: require completion of Phase 1 before implementation, enforce single-hypothesis rules, mandate explicit actions on fix failure." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Structural requirements (you can't proceed without X) are harder to bypass than textual suggestions (you should do X)" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_f7b59b63 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When extracting and structuring any skill from informal source material" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Extract core framework from source material 2. Decide what to include (rules, anti-shortcuts, pressure-resistant language, concrete steps) vs leave out (project-specific context, repetition, narrative) 3. Structure following skill-creation template 4. Add bulletproofing elements 5. Test under multiple pressure scenarios 6. Iterate based on test results" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

